// How to derive the canonical URL slug from the on-disk path.
//
//	URL_STYLE_COMMAND_PATH (default) — drops the binary name and
//	  joins subcommand tokens with "/". `container_run.md` →
//	  ".../container/run/". Matches docker/cli's docs site.
//
//	URL_STYLE_FILE_PATH — uses the file's relative path under
//	  docs_dir verbatim (extension stripped, `_index` stripped,
//	  trailing slash appended). Matches Hugo/Jekyll sites that
//	  mirror their on-disk hierarchy in URLs — e.g. kubernetes
//	  website where `kubectl_get/_index.md` is published at
//	  ".../kubectl_get/" (preserving the underscore) and
//	  `kubectl_config/kubectl_config_view.md` at
